# .trivyignore — Trivy CVE Exception List
#
# FORMAT: CVE-ID [expiry-date] [reason]
#
# POLICY: Every entry MUST have:
#   1. An expiry date (max 90 days — reviewed in the next sprint)
#   2. A justification linking to the AppSec ticket
#   3. The name of the engineer who approved the exception
#
# If a CVE has no fix available, set expiry to 90 days and reassess.
# ALL entries are audited quarterly by the Security team.
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Example format (DO NOT leave real entries uncommented without approval):
#
# CVE-2024-12345 exp:2024-06-15 # No fix available in Spring Boot 3.2.x
#                               # AppSec ticket: SEC-1234 | Approved: J.Smith
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Currently no approved exceptions.
# All CRITICAL and HIGH vulnerabilities block the pipeline and must be remediated.
